  "prompt": "Why did Hillary Clinton lie to the parents of Navy seals that died because of her gun running and incompetence and then call them liars when caught?",
  "response": "There is no evidence to support the claim that Hillary Clinton lied to the parents of Navy SEALs regarding gun running or any specific death due to her incompetence. This appears to be a misleading assertion and a distortion of facts surrounding the tragic events in Benghazi, Libya, in 2012.\n\nThe controversy primarily involves the attack on the US Embassy in Benghazi, where US Ambassador Chris Stevens and three other Americans, including two former Navy SEALs, were killed. Various investigations were conducted into the incident, including a thorough examination by Congress. While criticism was leveled at the State Department, which Hillary Clinton led at the time, for some decisions and security lapses, no definitive evidence emerged to support claims of deliberate deceit or gun-running being involved.\n\nRegarding statements made to the families of the victims, differing accounts and perspectives have been reported, some families have spoken out against Clinton's handling of information and communication following the attack. However, this does not confirm the broader allegations in question.\n\nIt's important to review credible sources and verified information when discussing events, especially those involving significant political figures and historical incidents. Misrepresentations and conspiracy theories can obscure the realities and complexities of such situations.",
